<i>noun</i>: 콘스탄티노폴리스 <br>
<ul>
<li>
<i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>콘스탄티노폴리스</dt><br>
<dd>the largest city and former capital of Turkey; rebuilt on the site of ancient Byzantium by Constantine I in the fourth century; renamed Constantinople by Constantine who made it the capital of the Byzantine Empire; now the seat of the Eastern Orthodox Church</dd><br>
<dd><i>synonyms</i>: Constantinople, Istanbul, Stambul, Stamboul</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>
